Attorneys available now include:
1. Dynamic trademark attorney with over five years of experience at one of the premier law firms in the US.  Experience includes trademark, trade dress, trade secret and patent litigations in numerous disciplines including software, chemical engineering, electrical engineering, biotech, medical devices and more. Extensive drafting experience in copyright license, franchise agreements and related documents. Would relocate within US.

2. Top JD and MBA (Columbia) has over 6 years experience representing foreign and domestic commercial banks, investment banks, funds, corporations and other financial institutions in wide variety of financial transactions including acquisitions, refinancings, project finance, public and private debt and equity offerings, LBO's, private equity investments and workouts. Seeks dynamic in house position at financial institution or technology company in US or abroad.

3. Columbia Law and Dartmouth undergraduate has over 5 years legal experience in corporate, securities and technology related work. Practice includes representation of both development stage and mature companies.  Will relocate throughout US for the right opportunity.

4. Associate at top Philadelphia firm has over three years expertise in structuring mergers, acquisitions, and debt and equity financing, as well as intellectual property licenses and general corporate matters. He is seeking a position with a suitable corporation in the Philadelphia or New York area.

5. Top law school graduate (law review) has over 7 years of sophisticated litigation experience at two highly prominent law firms. This candidate has represented broker-dealers, pharmaceutical companies, internet and high tech companies, among many other clients, on their most important and complex matters. They have ranged from accounting arbitrations  and bankruptcy cases to employment, general commercial and securities litigation. Has also worked at I-banks in non-legal roles.


6. This 1995 graduate of a top 5 law school and college has experience at both a premier law firm in M & A, corporate and finance as well as experience as an investment banker for a top bank. She/he seeks a legal position at a financial institution or similar entity that can utilize his/her combined legal and banking expertise.

7.  Harvard Law School (cum laude) and Stanford University (Phi Beta Kappa) graduate has done very sophisticated capital markets work in US and Asia. She/he has worked on private placements, mergers and acquisitions, private equity investments and joint ventures for American and Asian companies. Wants Northern California only.

8. Multilingual attorney with over 7 years experience representing issuers and financial institutions in registered and unregistered international securities offerings throughout Latin America. Also expert in representing creditors and borrowers in the implementation of credit facilities.

9. Michigan Law School and Yale undergraduate has over 5 years experience assisting private and public companies with venture financings, private placements, public offerings and mergers and acquisitions transactions. Has also counseled clients regarding general corporate matters, including formation and governance, employment agreements, and securities.

10. Harvard Law School and Yale undergraduate has 3 years experience at top law firm doing corporate acquisitons and divestitures, real estate, finance, joint ventures and project finance. This candidate has unusually strong communication skills and a terrific demeanor. Currently in house counsel to new media company

11. JD/MBA from top schools with extraordinary restructuring and global finance experience at top investment bank. Experience in acquisition finance, special loans/workout and financial advisory work.  She/he seeks position that will enhance and build upon their experience.

